    "The findings indicate that GeoGebra-related studies appeared in SCOPUS starting from 2007.",
    "Although there is a general trend toward an increase in the number of publications over the years, with a notable peak in 2022 with 54 articles, there were also periods of decline, such as in 2014 with 9 articles and in 2023 with 36 articles.",
    "This suggests that the growth trajectory is not consistently upward, indicating a nonsharp rate of growth in GeoGebra research.",
    "These findings highlight the necessity for further studies on GeoGebra.",
    "These results are consistent with the study by Gökçe and Güner (2022), which focused on studies from 2009 to 2021 in the Web of Science database."
